Acne rosacea is a chronic relapsing skin condition affecting the face, characterized by recurrent episodes of facial flushing, erythema, telangiectasia, papules and pustules. There may be eye symptoms (ocular rosacea), which are usually bilateral.

Documents.MetaDescription: Amenorrhoea is the absence or cessation of menstruation. Primary amenorrhoea is defined as the failure to establish menstruation by 15 years of age in girls with normal secondary sexual characteristics (such as breast development), or by 13 years of age in girls with no secondary sexual characteristics.
